{"timestamp": "2025-12-03 10:06:39.187689", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting diagnosis report — multi-tier Clos EBGP fabric\\n\\nSummary / overall health\\n- Control-plane: FRR BGP sessions are established across the fabric (super-spine ↔ spines ↔ leaves). Summaries from the super-spine, spines and leaves show neighbors are Up and exchanging prefixes. Routing tables on routers include the expected 10.<pod>.<leaf>.0/24 host subnets; I see full BGP visibility across the routers.\\n- Data-plane: Most host-to-host reachability checks succeeded (pings between many PCs completed with low RTT and no loss).\\n- Exception: One host (pc_0_1) is not participating in traffic and some reachability tests from it were not executed (status \"unknown\").\\n\\nAnomalies detected\\n1. Host pc_0_1 appears isolated — no L2/L3 traffic observed on its interface and a missing default route.\\n   - pc_0_1 ifconfig shows eth0 configured as 10.0.1.2/24 but RX packets = 0 and TX packets = 0.\\n     - Evidence: pc_0_1 ifconfig excerpt: \"eth0 ... inet 10.0.1.2 ... RX packets 0 bytes 0 ... TX packets 0 bytes 0\"\\n   - pc_0_1\\'s route table contains only the local connected route (10.0.1.0/24); there is no default gateway entry on pc_0_1.\\n     - Evidence: pc_0_1 ip_route: \"10.0.1.0/24 dev eth0 proto kernel scope link src 10.0.1.2\" (no default route).\\n   - Pings initiated from pc_0_1 to other PCs returned status \"unknown\" in the reachability summary (i.e., probes from pc_0_1 did not run/complete).\\n\\n2. Corresponding leaf interface shows no traffic\\n   - leaf_router_0_1 eth8 (10.0.1.1) shows RX packets = 0 and TX packets = 0, indicating no L2/L3 frames crossing that link.\\n     - Evidence: leaf_router_0_1 ifconfig excerpt: \"eth8 ... inet 10.0.1.1 ... RX packets 0 bytes 0 ... TX packets 0 bytes 0\"\\n   - For comparison, the other leaf->host link (leaf_router_0_0:eth8 <-> pc_0_0) shows normal packet counters (pc_0_0 has non-zero RX/TX and leaf_router_0_0 eth8 shows RX/TX > 0), demonstrating that other host links are operational.\\n\\nBGP / routing findings (control-plane)\\n- leaf_router_0_0 and leaf_router_0_1 both have established BGP neighbors (sessions Up, neighbor counts expected).\\n  - Example: leaf_router_0_1 BGP summary lists 8 neighbors, all Up, PfxRcd values present (peers reporting ~31 prefixes).\\n- Super-spine and spine routers report many neighbors and route entries; the super-spine\\'s BGP table shows many peers and the routing outputs show routes for all 10.x/24 subnets.\\n- Router forwarding tables (show ip route outputs) show selected BGP routes for 10.* networks and connected /31 inter-router subnets — no obvious control-plane convergence or missing global routes.\\n\\nFault localization\\n- Primary affected devices/links:\\n  1. pc_0_1 (host) — eth0 shows no RX/TX and missing default route.\\n  2. leaf_router_0_1: interface eth8 (10.0.1.1) — shows no RX/TX on that interface.\\n\\nProbable root cause(s)\\n- Most likely cause: Layer-1/Layer-2 connectivity issue between pc_0_1 and leaf_router_0_1 (physical cable, virtual link, switch port down, or interface administratively down). Both ends (pc and leaf) are configured with IPs in the same /24, but neither shows any packet counters on the connecting interface, consistent with a disconnected link.\\n- Contributing/masked symptom: pc_0_1 lacks a default route (no gateway configured). Even if the host had an IP and link up, missing default route would prevent reachability to remote subnets; however the immediate root cause of zero traffic counters is the link-level failure. The absent default route on pc_0_1 is an additional configuration issue observed in the host\\'s routing table.\\n\\nSupporting evidence (selected)\\n- pc_0_1 ifconfig / ip route:\\n  - eth0: inet 10.0.1.2/24, RX packets 0, TX packets 0\\n  - ip route: \"10.0.1.0/24 dev eth0 proto kernel scope link src 10.0.1.2\" (no default)\\n- leaf_router_0_1 ifconfig / ip route:\\n  - eth8: inet 10.0.1.1/24, RX packets 0, TX packets 0\\n  - ip route shows 10.0.1.0/24 on eth8 (connected)\\n- Reachability summary:\\n  - Many host-to-host pings successful (loss_percent 0.0), but pc_0_1-originated tests are \"unknown\".\\n\\nConfidence and notes\\n- Confidence that the rest of the fabric is healthy (BGP sessions up, routes present, host-to-host pings across fabric successful): high.\\n- Confidence that pc_0_1 is isolated due to a local link-level issue between pc_0_1 and leaf_router_0_1: high (direct packet counter evidence on both endpoints).\\n- The missing default route on pc_0_1 is definite (observed) and would prevent remote connectivity even if the link were up; however the immediate cause of zero counters is best explained by physical/data-link disconnection.\\n\\nNo mitigations included in this report. If you want, I can next run targeted tests (ARP table checks, ethtool on the interfaces, or bring up/down checks) to further narrow the L1/L2 cause., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='c1e3983b-c018-472e-abca-26c188cab8c6'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5-mini", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
